(iv) For characteristic wastes D001, D002, and D012&hyph;D043 that are: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subject to the treatment standards in &sect;268.40 (other than those 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
expressed as a required method of treatment); that are reasonably 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
expected to contain underlying hazardous constituents as defined in &sect;268.2(i); are treated on-site to remove
the hazardous characteristic; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and are then sent off-site for treatment of underlying hazardous constituents, the certification must state the
following: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 04 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=1 -->
I certify under penalty of law that the waste has been 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
treated in accordance with the requirements of 40 CFR 268.40 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to remove the hazardous characteristic. This 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
decharacterized waste contains underlying hazardous 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
constituents that require further treatment to meet 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
universal treatment standards. I am aware that there are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
significant penalties for submitting a false certification, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
including the possibility of fine and imprisonment. 
