<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
22. In &sect;268.9, paragraph (a), (d)(1)(i), and (d)(1)(ii) are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
revised, (d)(1)(iii) is removed and (d)(2) (i) and (ii) are added to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
read as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;268.9 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Special rules regarding wastes that exhibit a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
characteristic. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The initial generator of a solid waste must determine each 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
EPA Hazardous Waste Number (waste code) applicable to the waste in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
order to determine the applicable treatment standards under subpart D 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of this part. For purposes of part 268, the waste will carry the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
waste code for any applicable listing under 40 CFR part 261, subpart 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
D. In addition, the waste will carry one or more of the waste codes 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under 40 CFR part 261, subpart C, where the waste exhibits a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
characteristic, except in the case when the treatment standard for the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
waste code listed in 40 CFR part 261, subpart D operates in lieu of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the treatment standard for the waste code under 40 CFR part 261, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subpart C, as specified in paragraph (b) of this section. If the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
generator determines that his waste displays the characteristic of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
ignitability (D001) (and is not in the High TOC Ignitable Liquids 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Subcategory or is not treated by CMBST, or RORGS), or the waste code listed in 40 CFR part 261, subpart D operates in lieu
of the treatment standard for the waste code under 40 CFR part 261, subpart C, as specified in paragraph (b) of this section.
If the generator determines that his waste displays the characteristic of ignitability (D001) (and is not in the High
TOC Ignitable Liquids Subcategory or is not treated by CMBST, or RORGS), or the characteristic of corrosivity (D002),
and is prohibited under &sect;268.37; or that his waste displays the characteristic of toxicity 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(D012&hyph;D043), and is prohibited under &sect;268.38, the generator must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determine the underlying hazardous constituents (as defined in &sect;268.2), in the D001, D002, or D012&hyph;D043
wastes. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

